1
00:00:47,560 --> 00:00:56,559

2
00:01:51,524 --> 00:01:53,458
My dear children.

3
00:01:53,993 --> 00:01:59,056
It is now better than several years since I moved to New York

4
00:01:59,165 --> 00:02:02,657
and I haven't seen you as much as I would like to.

5
00:02:03,736 --> 00:02:07,502
I hope you will come to this ceremony of papal honours,

6
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:09,938
given for my charitable work.

7
00:02:10,043 --> 00:02:12,170

8
00:02:12,312 --> 00:02:15,645
The only wealth in this world is children.

9
00:02:15,748 --> 00:02:18,876
More than all the money and power on earth.

10
00:02:19,619 --> 00:02:21,849
You are my treasure.

11
00:02:23,556 --> 00:02:25,922
Anthony and Mary,

12
00:02:26,059 --> 00:02:30,826
although I entrusted your education to your mother for your own best interest,

13
00:02:31,097 --> 00:02:33,588
I look forward to seeing you,

14
00:02:33,700 --> 00:02:37,898
and to a new period of harmony in our lives.

15
00:02:38,304 --> 00:02:43,435
perhaps you might prevail upon your mother to come to this celebration,

16
00:02:43,543 --> 00:02:49,607
and that from time to time, we can all see each other at family functions.

17
00:02:49,749 --> 00:02:55,779
Anyway, I remain your loving father.

18
00:03:24,083 --> 00:03:26,551
Hail Mary, full of grace...

19
00:03:30,123 --> 00:03:32,091
...blessed art Thou amongst women...

20
00:03:33,526 --> 00:03:36,222
...and blessed is the fruit of Thy womb, Jesus.

21
00:03:37,864 --> 00:03:40,355
Holy Mary, mother of God,

22
00:03:40,900 --> 00:03:42,561
pray for us sinners...

23
00:04:06,693 --> 00:04:12,791
Almighty God, bless the insignia of Saint Sebastian the Martyr,

24
00:04:12,899 --> 00:04:19,361
that it may contribute to the sacredness of him to whom it is given.

25
00:04:31,818 --> 00:04:35,549
Do you, Michael, promise to be faithful

26
00:04:35,655 --> 00:04:38,647
to the noble purposes of this Order,

27
00:04:38,758 --> 00:04:43,923
to have a special care for the poor, the needy and those who are ill?

28
00:04:44,030 --> 00:04:45,520
I do so promise.

29
00:05:01,214 --> 00:05:05,708
May the blessing of Almighty God, Father,

30
00:05:05,818 --> 00:05:11,085
Son and Holy Spirit descend upon you

31
00:05:11,224 --> 00:05:14,819
and remain with you forever.

32
00:05:14,994 --> 00:05:16,188

33
00:06:48,287 --> 00:06:50,983
Vincent, our name is not on the list.

34
00:06:53,559 --> 00:06:55,356
Write it in. Mancini.

35
00:06:55,461 --> 00:06:57,656
M-A-N-C-I-N-I.

36
00:06:59,532 --> 00:07:00,521
Problem?

37
00:07:00,633 --> 00:07:01,895
My name isn't on the list.

38
00:07:02,001 --> 00:07:05,266
Then you have to leave immediately.

39
00:07:05,371 --> 00:07:06,929
You want to dance with me?

40
00:07:07,106 --> 00:07:10,132
Joe, it's Vinnie. These are our guests.

41
00:07:10,243 --> 00:07:12,234
I'm sorry. I'm sorry, sir.

42
00:07:12,345 --> 00:07:14,438
Welcome to the party.

43
00:08:07,934 --> 00:08:09,424
it's good to see you.

44
00:08:09,535 --> 00:08:11,560
Good to see you. This is my husband.

45
00:08:11,671 --> 00:08:14,231
-Sit down.
-My son, Anthony.

46
00:08:15,341 --> 00:08:19,539
The Order of Saint Sebastian is one of the highest honours the Church awards.

47
00:08:19,645 --> 00:08:20,805

48
00:08:20,913 --> 00:08:23,609
it was first granted by Pope...

49
00:08:23,716 --> 00:08:26,446
What about Mr Corleone's connections with gambling?

50
00:08:26,719 --> 00:08:28,880
The press kits have...

51
00:08:28,988 --> 00:08:30,853
And involvement with the underworld?

52
00:08:30,957 --> 00:08:32,652
Cut the crap.

53
00:08:33,125 --> 00:08:38,722
The Pope, the Holy Father himself, has today blessed Michael Corleone.

54
00:08:38,831 --> 00:08:40,856
Do you know better than the Pope?

55
00:08:42,034 --> 00:08:43,296
Vincent!

56
00:08:43,402 --> 00:08:45,962
-She loves you.
-Yeah?

57
00:08:50,609 --> 00:08:52,338
I love you too.

58
00:08:57,950 --> 00:09:01,545
Hi, Vincent. I remember you.

59
00:09:02,655 --> 00:09:04,646
From where?

60
00:09:04,790 --> 00:09:06,849
The last party we were at together.

61
00:09:06,993 --> 00:09:08,426
Did you come to the club?

62
00:09:08,527 --> 00:09:10,119
No, it was a wedding.

63
00:09:10,229 --> 00:09:11,662

64
00:09:12,365 --> 00:09:15,562
I was eight and you were 15.

65
00:09:16,002 --> 00:09:19,028
I had many girifriends when I was 15.

66
00:09:19,105 --> 00:09:20,094
8 year olds?

67
00:09:20,172 --> 00:09:21,696
Especially them.

68
00:09:23,542 --> 00:09:25,305
Where's Mary?

69
00:09:25,878 --> 00:09:30,372
Would somebody please hail Mary? Excuse me, Your Excellency.

70
00:09:30,883 --> 00:09:35,377
You haven't kissed me hello yet. Relatives always kiss.

71
00:09:35,521 --> 00:09:36,818
Now we're related?

72
00:09:36,922 --> 00:09:38,651
I'm your little cousin.

73
00:09:46,465 --> 00:09:48,023
Who's your father?

74
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:52,603
I'll give you a hint. He's Italian.

75
00:09:52,705 --> 00:09:53,865

76
00:09:53,973 --> 00:09:56,134
Mary, we've been waiting for you.

77
00:09:56,275 --> 00:10:00,405
Remember to keep your voice low.

78
00:10:00,513 --> 00:10:03,573
And smile. Don't forget to smile.

79
00:10:21,233 --> 00:10:27,468
The honorary chairman of the Vito Corleone Foundation:

80
00:10:27,573 --> 00:10:30,064
my daughter, Mary Corleone.

81
00:10:39,752 --> 00:10:42,084
Thanks.

82
00:10:42,521 --> 00:10:46,252
I think I inherited my father's love for speechmaking.

83
00:10:46,358 --> 00:10:47,848
Here it goes.

84
00:10:48,994 --> 00:10:53,624
The Vito Corleone Foundation helps the poor in every country,

85
00:10:53,732 --> 00:10:57,998
gives grants to artists, funds medical research,

86
00:10:58,137 --> 00:11:02,972
and is particularly dedicated to the resurrection of Sicily.

87
00:11:03,476 --> 00:11:05,535
Archbishop Gilday,

88
00:11:05,644 --> 00:11:08,636
here is 100 million dollars

89
00:11:08,747 --> 00:11:10,237
for the poor of Sicily,

90
00:11:10,349 --> 00:11:12,078
in the name of Vito Corleone.

91
00:11:12,685 --> 00:11:14,778
Don't spend it all in one place.

92
00:11:33,072 --> 00:11:38,806
Mary, I'm so proud of you.

93
00:11:45,284 --> 00:11:46,478
Michael...

94
00:11:47,052 --> 00:11:49,714
You've done a wonderful thing for Sicily.

95
00:11:50,656 --> 00:11:54,285
Let's hope that the money gets to the people who need it.

96
00:11:54,560 --> 00:11:55,891
Amen.

97
00:11:55,995 --> 00:11:58,020
...the most important part:

98
00:11:58,764 --> 00:12:01,232
Johnny Fontane!

99
00:12:09,642 --> 00:12:11,405
Thank you very much.

100
00:12:11,510 --> 00:12:14,274
I'm happy to be here. I would like you to join me

101
00:12:14,380 --> 00:12:18,976
in honouring Commendatore Michael Corleone.

102
00:12:22,788 --> 00:12:26,121
I have something special for our godfather.

103
00:12:26,225 --> 00:12:28,591
I happen to know his favourite song.

104
00:12:28,727 --> 00:12:29,716
Michael, where are you going?

105
00:12:29,828 --> 00:12:31,193

106
00:12:31,297 --> 00:12:34,357
I'm off to the kitchen to hear some Tony Bennett records.

107
00:12:35,901 --> 00:12:38,392
Your favourite song: "Salsiccia's Own".

108
00:12:38,504 --> 00:12:41,371
I'm having a salsiccia sandwich. I'll be back.

109
00:12:46,212 --> 00:12:51,582

110
00:12:51,684 --> 00:12:57,520

111
00:12:57,623 --> 00:13:04,051

112
00:13:04,597 --> 00:13:08,590

113
00:13:16,175 --> 00:13:17,437
Hello, kay.

114
00:13:27,920 --> 00:13:31,378
Congratulations, Michael. That's quite an honour.

115
00:13:31,490 --> 00:13:34,015
But a little expensive, wouldn't you say?

116
00:13:36,895 --> 00:13:38,260
Cake?

117
00:13:38,764 --> 00:13:40,391
No, thank you.

118
00:13:54,413 --> 00:13:57,007
-it's been a long time, hasn't it?
-Yeah.

119
00:13:57,116 --> 00:13:59,414
-Eight years.
-Yeah.

120
00:13:59,752 --> 00:14:02,050
You look wonderful.

121
00:14:05,224 --> 00:14:07,715
Your son has something he wants to talk to you about.

122
00:14:07,826 --> 00:14:09,589
I came here for him.

123
00:14:18,971 --> 00:14:25,308

124
00:14:25,411 --> 00:14:30,849

125
00:14:30,949 --> 00:14:35,283

126
00:14:44,797 --> 00:14:45,786
What's wrong with being a lawyer?

127
00:14:45,898 --> 00:14:47,729

128
00:14:47,833 --> 00:14:51,132
He wants his life to be in music.

129
00:14:52,004 --> 00:14:54,097
Music is great, I love music.

130
00:14:54,206 --> 00:14:56,299
But he should finish what he started.

131
00:14:56,408 --> 00:14:57,932
Anthony...

132
00:14:58,310 --> 00:14:59,800
I'm going my own way.

133
00:14:59,912 --> 00:15:01,345
Your own way?

134
00:15:01,747 --> 00:15:03,112
-Professional singer?
-Yes.

135
00:15:03,782 --> 00:15:06,808
What happens if you fail?

136
00:15:06,919 --> 00:15:08,682
I won't fail.

137
00:15:08,821 --> 00:15:10,288
Men always believe that.

138
00:15:10,356 --> 00:15:11,345

139
00:15:11,423 --> 00:15:15,154
A law degree is like taking out insurance.

140
00:15:15,260 --> 00:15:16,659
After that you can...

141
00:15:16,762 --> 00:15:19,424
-work for me...
-I will never work for you.

142
00:15:20,366 --> 00:15:22,391
I have bad memories.

143
00:15:24,002 --> 00:15:27,631
Every family has bad memories.

144
00:15:30,442 --> 00:15:32,501
I'll always be your son,

145
00:15:32,611 --> 00:15:35,876
but won't have anything to do with your business.

146
00:15:37,416 --> 00:15:41,716
Anthony... finish the law degree.

147
00:15:42,388 --> 00:15:43,912
No.

148
00:16:01,073 --> 00:16:06,409
Well, that he got from you. That "no".

149
00:16:07,980 --> 00:16:11,279
You could've helped me convince him.

150
00:16:11,517 --> 00:16:13,815
Convince him of what?

151
00:16:13,919 --> 00:16:15,250
Of what?

152
00:16:15,854 --> 00:16:18,584
He throws his life away.

153
00:16:18,757 --> 00:16:21,351
He throws greatness away.

154
00:16:21,627 --> 00:16:23,561
This is greatness?

155
00:16:24,763 --> 00:16:28,096
Now that you're so respectable, you're more dangerous than ever.

156
00:16:28,233 --> 00:16:34,604
I preferred you when you were just a common Mafia hood.

157
00:16:34,706 --> 00:16:39,700
-Can we talk common sense here?
-All right.

158
00:16:39,812 --> 00:16:41,006
Okay.

159
00:16:47,352 --> 00:16:49,912
Tony knows that you killed Fredo.

160
00:16:56,628 --> 00:16:57,925
What did you come here for?

161
00:16:58,030 --> 00:17:00,055
To protect my son.

162
00:17:00,165 --> 00:17:02,759
Not to see you disguised by your church.

163
00:17:02,868 --> 00:17:05,928
That was a shameful ceremony.

164
00:17:09,608 --> 00:17:12,634
I spent my life protecting my son.

165
00:17:12,744 --> 00:17:16,441
I spent my life protecting my family!

166
00:17:16,548 --> 00:17:18,846
Let's be reasonable, okay?

167
00:17:19,618 --> 00:17:23,019
That's your big thing, isn't it, Michael?

168
00:17:23,222 --> 00:17:27,989
Reason. Backed up by murder.

169
00:17:30,529 --> 00:17:33,089
Oh, God. You hate me. You hate me.

170
00:17:33,198 --> 00:17:36,065
No. I don't hate you.

171
00:17:37,603 --> 00:17:39,969
I dread you.

172
00:17:43,108 --> 00:17:44,268
I did what I could, kay,

173
00:17:44,443 --> 00:17:47,879
to protect all of you

174
00:17:48,013 --> 00:17:50,573
from the horrors of this world.

175
00:17:50,682 --> 00:17:53,549
But you became my horror.

176
00:18:02,628 --> 00:18:07,065
The children still love you, though. Especially Mary.

177
00:18:09,034 --> 00:18:15,735
That's something. We can build on that.

178
00:18:15,874 --> 00:18:17,739
For their sake.

179
00:18:20,812 --> 00:18:22,643
Let's try.

180
00:18:22,748 --> 00:18:26,582
Only if you let Tony go free to have his own life,

181
00:18:26,985 --> 00:18:28,953
away from you.

182
00:18:35,427 --> 00:18:37,588
I'll let Tony go.

183
00:18:39,831 --> 00:18:41,526
Thank you.

184
00:19:15,934 --> 00:19:17,959
-Hi.
-Hi.

185
00:19:20,005 --> 00:19:22,803
You could hurt somebody with those.

186
00:19:23,308 --> 00:19:25,333
Let me show you around.

187
00:19:25,444 --> 00:19:27,878
Can you get me an interview with Corleone?

188
00:19:27,980 --> 00:19:32,974
No. I'm a relative, but I can't do that. What else can I do for you?

189
00:19:33,685 --> 00:19:35,209
Handsome, but useless.

190
00:19:35,320 --> 00:19:36,617
Oh, yeah?

191
00:19:36,722 --> 00:19:37,984
That's okay, I'll gamble.

192
00:19:38,090 --> 00:19:40,991
Do you like to gamble? Let's go to Atlantic City.

193
00:19:41,093 --> 00:19:43,493
I'll show you how to gamble.

194
00:19:43,595 --> 00:19:46,325
How do I know what numbers to bet?

195
00:19:46,431 --> 00:19:48,422
Do I look like a loser?

196
00:19:48,567 --> 00:19:55,063
Well... Spooky-looking guy there.

197
00:19:55,173 --> 00:19:58,199
What's a guy like that doing here?

198
00:19:58,310 --> 00:19:59,800
That's Joey Zasa's bulldog.

199
00:19:59,878 --> 00:20:00,867
You know him?

200
00:20:00,946 --> 00:20:02,470
Yeah, I do.

201
00:20:02,948 --> 00:20:05,781
His name is Anthony Squigilaro.

202
00:20:05,884 --> 00:20:07,647
They call him "The Ant".

203
00:20:07,986 --> 00:20:10,784
He dips his bullets in cyanide.

204
00:20:19,297 --> 00:20:21,162
Don Altobello.

205
00:20:22,534 --> 00:20:25,059
I've come to pay my respects.

206
00:20:25,170 --> 00:20:26,694
Grazie.

207
00:20:29,341 --> 00:20:31,707
You honour my father's friendship.

208
00:20:32,210 --> 00:20:34,678
Where is my goddaughter?

209
00:20:35,881 --> 00:20:38,645
-Constanza!
-Don Altobello.

210
00:20:38,850 --> 00:20:43,844
it was not so long ago that I held you in these old hands.

211
00:20:45,724 --> 00:20:47,089

212
00:20:47,225 --> 00:20:48,556

213
00:20:48,660 --> 00:20:51,458

214
00:20:51,563 --> 00:20:56,899
Michael, I've lost all the venom, all the juice of youth.

215
00:20:57,002 --> 00:21:00,028
I've lost the lust for women,

216
00:21:00,138 --> 00:21:02,663
and now my mind is clear.

217
00:21:02,774 --> 00:21:05,800
My duty to God is clear.

218
00:21:05,911 --> 00:21:10,075
I have a special favour to ask of you.

219
00:21:10,649 --> 00:21:18,146
Can I attach my name to the Vito Corleone Foundation,

220
00:21:18,290 --> 00:21:24,490
so that you and I can be joined in name and spirit?

221
00:21:25,864 --> 00:21:27,957
-One million dollars.
-Oh, my!

222
00:21:33,605 --> 00:21:34,765
Godfather.

223
00:21:34,873 --> 00:21:37,808
Don Altobello, you have such a heart.

224
00:21:40,645 --> 00:21:45,480
Come, let's go and sample some of that old vino.

225
00:21:51,656 --> 00:21:55,057
The Vatican knows nothing about these shareholders.

226
00:21:55,160 --> 00:21:56,320
Good.

227
00:21:56,428 --> 00:21:58,521
I have a tendency to worry.

228
00:21:58,630 --> 00:22:02,464
We've increased our position substantially. Naturally, I worry.

229
00:22:02,601 --> 00:22:06,935
Stop worrying, we have an agreement.

230
00:22:07,038 --> 00:22:09,939
Good. How do you think I got this grey hair?

231
00:22:10,075 --> 00:22:13,476
Two seconds...

232
00:22:13,578 --> 00:22:15,944
Thank you for your contribution to the swimming-pool.

233
00:22:16,047 --> 00:22:20,211
We need your help on Sam Wallace's candidacy for judgeship.

234
00:22:20,318 --> 00:22:22,752
-We can always use a good judge.
-Thanks.

235
00:22:22,854 --> 00:22:24,287
Andrew!

236
00:22:24,723 --> 00:22:28,819
My godson Andrew Hagen. My brother Tom's eldest boy.

237
00:22:28,927 --> 00:22:33,193
He's been assistant to Bishop Breelan for three years.

238
00:22:33,298 --> 00:22:35,129
Hopes to be assigned to the Vatican.

239
00:22:35,233 --> 00:22:37,667
Rome needs fine young priests.

240
00:22:37,769 --> 00:22:41,227
His mother Theresa Hagen, Bishop Gilday.

241
00:22:41,706 --> 00:22:43,367
Honoured to meet you.

242
00:22:43,475 --> 00:22:46,273
Mr Corleone. Hi. Grace Hamiiton.

243
00:22:47,479 --> 00:22:50,073
Vincent Mancini promised to tell you about me.

244
00:22:50,182 --> 00:22:51,706
That maybe you'd see me.

245
00:22:52,384 --> 00:22:55,751
-Did Vincent Mancini call about her?
-No.

246
00:22:55,887 --> 00:22:58,048
You promised to stay out there,

247
00:22:58,123 --> 00:22:59,112
-I know.
-twice.

248
00:23:01,059 --> 00:23:03,050
Joey Zasa showed up.

249
00:23:03,161 --> 00:23:04,958
He's waiting in the lobby.

250
00:23:05,063 --> 00:23:09,466
He wants to personally congratulate you. Show his respect.

251
00:23:09,568 --> 00:23:11,160
Do I have to see him?

252
00:23:11,303 --> 00:23:12,930
He says you're his patron.

253
00:23:13,038 --> 00:23:15,029

254
00:23:17,943 --> 00:23:21,743
Hey, Vinnie! Who's your favourite aunt?

255
00:23:21,847 --> 00:23:23,109
You are.

256
00:23:26,251 --> 00:23:29,220
Today I'll talk to Michael about your little problem.

257
00:23:30,422 --> 00:23:34,153
if you'd warned me, I would have worn a better suit.

258
00:23:35,327 --> 00:23:41,391
The Meucci Association has elected you Italian-American Man of the Year.

259
00:23:41,867 --> 00:23:44,529
Meucci...

260
00:23:46,972 --> 00:23:48,667
Who's Meucci?

261
00:23:49,774 --> 00:23:52,242
The Italian-American who invented the telephone,

262
00:23:52,344 --> 00:23:55,905
one year before Bell.

263
00:23:59,784 --> 00:24:03,584
And this is the reason you've come today?

264
00:24:05,156 --> 00:24:07,181

265
00:24:10,061 --> 00:24:18,059
I... I've got a stone in my shoe.

266
00:24:18,236 --> 00:24:21,364
A two-bit punk who works for me.

267
00:24:21,506 --> 00:24:26,170
The one who thinks he's related to you.

268
00:24:27,279 --> 00:24:29,577
A bastard.

269
00:24:32,651 --> 00:24:33,913
He's here.

270
00:24:34,019 --> 00:24:38,080
Vincent Mancini. He's at the party.

271
00:24:40,358 --> 00:24:42,258
Bring him in.

272
00:24:43,361 --> 00:24:46,626
I think it's good that we talk.

273
00:24:46,731 --> 00:24:49,291
No, grazie.

274
