and focus and unlimited...

552
00:43:41,732 --> 00:43:42,994
Mr Corleone

553
00:43:43,100 --> 00:43:44,294
Mr Corleone, excuse me.

554
00:43:44,401 --> 00:43:48,531
Didn't you recently deposit 200 million

555
00:43:48,639 --> 00:43:49,901
in the Vatican Bank,

556
00:43:50,007 --> 00:43:52,840
which is affiliated with Immobiliare?

557
00:43:52,943 --> 00:43:54,274
True. Why not?

558
00:43:54,378 --> 00:43:57,176
Wasn't there any questioning about the timing

559
00:43:57,281 --> 00:44:00,717
on this particular deposit?

560
00:44:00,818 --> 00:44:02,445
Mr Chairman, if I may?

561
00:44:04,755 --> 00:44:07,053
The Vito Andolini Corleone Foundation,

562
00:44:07,157 --> 00:44:09,318
of which Mary Corleone is chairman,

563
00:44:09,426 --> 00:44:12,884
has made an endowment of 100 million dollars.

564
00:44:12,996 --> 00:44:17,228
The money comes from his own family and will be administered by the Vatican.

565
00:44:17,334 --> 00:44:19,165
Does that answer your question?

566
00:44:20,037 --> 00:44:26,840
I have always believed that helping your fellow man is profitable in every sense,

567
00:44:26,944 --> 00:44:29,811
personally and bottom line.

568
00:44:29,913 --> 00:44:31,847
My fellow shareholders,

569
00:44:31,949 --> 00:44:35,350
if Europe and America can learn to co-operate,

570
00:44:35,486 --> 00:44:39,650
if we can learn to pool our wealth, share our markets,

571
00:44:39,756 --> 00:44:42,725
we can defeat any competition

572
00:44:42,826 --> 00:44:45,351
anywhere in the world.

573
00:44:45,462 --> 00:44:48,260
Thank you for your time.

574
00:44:48,365 --> 00:44:53,428
I hope that you will look favourably on my proposal. Thank you.

575
00:44:59,143 --> 00:45:01,134
Let me have this microphone here.

576
00:45:01,245 --> 00:45:04,772
Will we let a criminal run our company?

577
00:45:04,882 --> 00:45:07,749
He's got the map of Sicily on his face!

578
00:45:07,818 --> 00:45:08,807
Order!

579
00:45:08,886 --> 00:45:10,751
He's either a Catholic or a mafioso...

580
00:45:13,624 --> 00:45:17,788
The Hamiiton Investors Group cannot support this proposal.

581
00:45:18,795 --> 00:45:20,422
Your excellency...

582
00:45:21,298 --> 00:45:23,061
Mr Chairman...

583
00:45:23,500 --> 00:45:26,162
...the Vatican Bank feels

584
00:45:26,270 --> 00:45:30,934
that International Immobiliare...

585
00:45:31,642 --> 00:45:36,272
...will be safe in Mr Corleone's hands.

586
00:45:36,380 --> 00:45:39,508
...subject to audit and final ratification,

587
00:45:39,616 --> 00:45:41,277
which must take place in Rome.

588
00:45:41,385 --> 00:45:45,185
Please join me in welcoming Mr Michael Corleone.

589
00:45:55,232 --> 00:45:56,722
Dad?

590
00:45:59,236 --> 00:46:02,763
Tony says that I'm a front for the foundation.

591
00:46:04,141 --> 00:46:07,770
That you're using me to pull the strings.

592
00:46:07,945 --> 00:46:09,537
To get the money where you want it.

593
00:46:09,646 --> 00:46:11,273
Please!

594
00:46:11,415 --> 00:46:13,610
To shine up your public image.

595
00:46:13,717 --> 00:46:15,446
Mary!

596
00:46:15,586 --> 00:46:18,111
Mary, this is real. This foundation

597
00:46:18,222 --> 00:46:20,190
is real.

598
00:46:21,892 --> 00:46:27,057
I wanted Anthony to be part of it. I thought you would be together on this.

599
00:46:27,164 --> 00:46:29,098
I won't interfere.

600
00:46:29,199 --> 00:46:30,689
I'll help, but only if you ask.

601
00:46:30,801 --> 00:46:34,328
What is this really for?

602
00:46:34,504 --> 00:46:36,404
Why are you doing this?

603
00:46:36,506 --> 00:46:38,701
Why am I doing this?

604
00:46:39,443 --> 00:46:42,503
I'm doing this for my children.

605
00:46:42,613 --> 00:46:45,104
You're doing it for your children too.

606
00:46:45,215 --> 00:46:48,343
This foundation is supposed to help all people?

607
00:46:48,452 --> 00:46:50,750
That's the purpose.

608
00:46:50,887 --> 00:46:53,617
This is legitimate. Mary,

609
00:46:53,724 --> 00:46:56,750
I swear, this is legitimate.

610
00:46:59,763 --> 00:47:02,891
Dad, I want this to bring me closer to you.

611
00:47:11,108 --> 00:47:13,133
I would burn in hell

612
00:47:13,510 --> 00:47:15,944
to keep you safe.

613
00:47:29,159 --> 00:47:33,960
Go in the other car. I'll ride with Michael. Go, go, go.

614
00:47:47,978 --> 00:47:50,640
As your family's oldest friend,

615
00:47:50,781 --> 00:47:54,444
I'm always chosen to bring you messages.

616
00:47:56,219 --> 00:48:01,316
Tell me, Don Altobello.

617
00:48:01,425 --> 00:48:05,862
Your old partners are grateful for the money you made them.

618
00:48:05,962 --> 00:48:07,953
They worship you...

619
00:48:08,365 --> 00:48:15,203
...but their hearts are broken, because they think you abandoned them.

620
00:48:15,305 --> 00:48:19,867
They want to share your deal on Immobiliare,

621
00:48:19,976 --> 00:48:21,739
to be a family again.

622
00:48:21,845 --> 00:48:25,144
it can purify their money.

623
00:48:26,416 --> 00:48:28,475
This I cannot do.

624
00:48:30,987 --> 00:48:35,253
Immobiliare must be legitimate.

625
00:48:35,926 --> 00:48:42,058
I know. But they're unhappy.

626
00:48:42,999 --> 00:48:44,830
And you?

627
00:48:44,935 --> 00:48:48,803
I ask nothing for myself.

628
00:48:48,905 --> 00:48:51,169
Only peace in my old age.

629
00:48:51,274 --> 00:48:56,109
But I must please the world around me.

630
00:48:56,413 --> 00:49:00,873
Michael, your father was a reasonable man.

631
00:49:00,984 --> 00:49:03,350
Learn from him.

632
00:49:04,788 --> 00:49:08,884
I learned many things from my father.

633
00:49:13,697 --> 00:49:16,063
Call a meeting, my friend,

634
00:49:16,166 --> 00:49:20,432
so there are no debts or grudges.

635
00:49:20,570 --> 00:49:22,265
We will make the peace,

636
00:49:22,372 --> 00:49:24,465
you and I.

637
00:49:34,317 --> 00:49:40,119

638
00:49:40,857 --> 00:49:43,291
The Vatican announced today...

639
00:49:43,393 --> 00:49:46,294
that pope paul Vl

640
00:49:46,396 --> 00:49:49,331
has canceled his Sunday blessing...

641
00:49:49,433 --> 00:49:52,493
due to ill health.

642
00:49:52,602 --> 00:49:56,766
His physician has ordered total bedrest...

643
00:49:56,907 --> 00:50:01,606
and cessation of all activities.

644
00:50:03,046 --> 00:50:05,071
They've had a press conference.

645
00:50:05,215 --> 00:50:09,311
The Pope's condition is grave. "Gravissimo."

646
00:50:20,664 --> 00:50:30,096

647
00:50:35,712 --> 00:50:40,081
The purpose of this meeting is to ratify...

648
00:50:40,217 --> 00:50:45,154
the motion passed by our shareholders in New York.

649
00:50:46,089 --> 00:50:47,852
Please...

650
00:50:48,358 --> 00:50:52,954
Our group represents a consortium of Catholic businessmen

651
00:50:53,063 --> 00:50:56,692
against the Corleone control.

652
00:50:56,800 --> 00:50:59,166
The Vatican has cast its vote.

653
00:50:59,269 --> 00:51:02,261
Corleone Group already controls the Board.

654
00:51:02,372 --> 00:51:04,237
According to the Lateran Treaty,

655
00:51:04,341 --> 00:51:07,970
the Vatican vote must be ratified here. Here in Rome,

656
00:51:08,078 --> 00:51:09,773
by the Pope.

657
00:51:13,149 --> 00:51:17,677
The Pope is gravely ill.

658
00:51:17,821 --> 00:51:20,016
Until he recovers,

659
00:51:20,290 --> 00:51:22,554
I am powerless.

660
00:51:22,659 --> 00:51:24,684
-What if he dies?
-Then...

661
00:51:24,861 --> 00:51:28,024
...as you Americans say,

662
00:51:28,131 --> 00:51:29,962
all bets are off.

663
00:51:30,066 --> 00:51:33,263
Gentlemen, please.

664
00:51:33,370 --> 00:51:37,864
This is a brief delay. Nothing more.

665
00:51:41,778 --> 00:51:45,305
Your Excellency, gentlemen...

666
00:51:45,415 --> 00:51:48,873
I advise you to join us in our prayers

667
00:51:48,985 --> 00:51:51,715
for the Holy Father's recovery.

668
00:51:52,055 --> 00:51:54,683
We had an agreement!

669
00:51:55,091 --> 00:51:59,050
This meeting was to be merely a formality.

670
00:51:59,162 --> 00:52:02,529
-Please sit down.
-I'd rather stand. Give me an answer.

671
00:52:02,632 --> 00:52:04,463

672
00:52:04,534 --> 00:52:08,197
The Immobiliare has its roots in the European tradition.

673
00:52:08,305 --> 00:52:10,671
Please understand.

674
00:52:10,774 --> 00:52:12,264
I understand.

675
00:52:12,375 --> 00:52:14,240
Your tactics are despicable.

676
00:52:14,344 --> 00:52:17,677
That's quite an indictment, coming from a Corleone.

677
00:52:17,781 --> 00:52:19,749
Gentlemen, gentlemen!

678
00:52:19,883 --> 00:52:22,613
Remember you are in the Vatican.

679
00:52:25,655 --> 00:52:28,123
What is it that you want?

680
00:52:28,224 --> 00:52:31,887
Yes, you will take control.

681
00:52:32,295 --> 00:52:35,924
We'll gladly put you at the helm of our little fleet,

682
00:52:36,466 --> 00:52:41,096
but our ships must all sail in the same direction.

683
00:52:41,972 --> 00:52:43,462
Otherwise,

684
00:52:43,573 --> 00:52:48,738
who can say how long your stay with us will last?

685
00:52:49,779 --> 00:52:51,747
it's not personal.

686
00:52:52,048 --> 00:52:56,849
it's only business. You should know, Godfather.

687
00:52:59,723 --> 00:53:02,021
Very well.

688
00:53:02,359 --> 00:53:04,884
You want to do business with me?

689
00:53:05,295 --> 00:53:08,196
I will do business with you.

690
00:53:08,465 --> 00:53:10,399
Vipers, all of them.

691
00:53:16,673 --> 00:53:18,368
We're back with the Borgias!

692
00:53:18,475 --> 00:53:21,444
-Uncle Michael...
-Andrew!

693
00:53:21,544 --> 00:53:24,206
I heard you were here. it's so nice to see you.

694
00:53:24,314 --> 00:53:27,283
Vincent, it's so nice.

695
00:53:27,417 --> 00:53:30,284
What is this about the Borgias? Those days are over.

696
00:53:36,192 --> 00:53:37,784
Recognise it?

697
00:53:37,894 --> 00:53:39,293
Yeah.

698
00:53:39,829 --> 00:53:41,592
Genco Olive Oil.

699
00:53:41,765 --> 00:53:43,630
That's where our grandfather started

700
00:53:43,733 --> 00:53:45,997
as a delivery boy.

701
00:53:46,102 --> 00:53:48,366
Three years later he owned it.

702
00:53:48,471 --> 00:53:49,563
Only in America.

703
00:53:49,673 --> 00:53:51,265
That's it.

704
00:53:51,708 --> 00:53:54,006
Vincenzo, where have you been hiding?

705
00:53:54,110 --> 00:53:55,600

706
00:53:55,712 --> 00:53:56,872
We need your help so badly.

707
00:53:56,980 --> 00:53:58,311
What can I do for you?

708
00:53:58,415 --> 00:53:59,780
Get rid of Joe Zasa.

709
00:53:59,883 --> 00:54:01,544
He sells drugs...

710
00:54:01,651 --> 00:54:03,448

711
00:54:03,586 --> 00:54:05,850
Now that I'm an older woman, I'm afraid to go out at night.

712
00:54:05,955 --> 00:54:08,185
Where should they be now?

713
00:54:08,458 --> 00:54:10,653
Lou, what's going on?

714
00:54:10,760 --> 00:54:12,022
We're late.

715
00:54:13,697 --> 00:54:14,721
Have I ever let you down?

716
00:54:14,831 --> 00:54:16,093
I trust you.

717
00:54:16,199 --> 00:54:17,257
Don't worry.

718
00:54:17,367 --> 00:54:18,698
Thank you.

719
00:54:18,802 --> 00:54:20,235
Enjoy yourselves.

720
00:54:27,043 --> 00:54:28,738
What was that?

721
00:54:29,479 --> 00:54:31,447
The neighbourhood's in trouble.

722
00:54:31,981 --> 00:54:33,471
Do you keep an eye out for them?

723
00:54:33,583 --> 00:54:34,811
Yes.

724
00:54:34,918 --> 00:54:36,283
And for me?

725
00:54:36,453 --> 00:54:37,977
From now on.

726
00:54:38,655 --> 00:54:40,020
I've missed you all this time.

727
00:54:40,123 --> 00:54:42,216
I missed you too, cousin.

728
00:54:42,726 --> 00:54:45,627
I missed growing up with my cousins.

729
00:54:45,729 --> 00:54:48,357
I didn't even know you, but missed you.

730
00:54:48,765 --> 00:54:53,395
Do you remember stories about our fathers? The old days?

731
00:54:53,503 --> 00:54:55,437
Yeah, what do you want to know?

732
00:54:58,174 --> 00:55:00,005
What was Sonny like?

733
00:55:02,212 --> 00:55:04,680
Well, he was the Prince of the City.

734
00:55:05,014 --> 00:55:06,538
He died before I was born,

735
00:55:06,649 --> 00:55:10,050
but I've heard a lot about him.

736
00:55:10,453 --> 00:55:12,546
What about my father?

737
00:55:12,655 --> 00:55:14,782
He's a great man.

738
00:55:15,658 --> 00:55:18,354
He's a hero. He saved the family.

739
00:55:19,896 --> 00:55:21,591
-Vincent?
-What?

740
00:55:21,698 --> 00:55:23,859
Did he kill his own brother?

741
00:55:28,404 --> 00:55:30,429
No.

742
00:55:32,308 --> 00:55:34,640
So, it's all lies?

743
00:55:38,314 --> 00:55:42,808
Just stories, sweetheart. Okay?

744
00:55:45,588 --> 00:55:47,749
Okay.

745
00:55:48,525 --> 00:55:50,720
I believe you.

746
00:55:51,494 --> 00:55:52,984
I'm glad you're around.

747
00:55:53,096 --> 00:55:55,223
I'm glad you're here too.

748
00:55:59,769 --> 00:56:02,033
Cugina...

749
00:56:02,238 --> 00:56:04,103
Cous...

750
00:56:18,054 --> 00:56:21,683
I'd like to take Joey Zasa for a ride in this and drop him.

751
00:56:21,791 --> 00:56:24,555
Joey Zasa is nothing.

752
00:56:24,661 --> 00:56:26,959
He's a small time enforcer.

753
00:56:27,063 --> 00:56:29,896
He bluffs and threatens. He's nothing.

754
00:56:29,999 --> 00:56:33,230
You can see him coming a mile away.

755
00:56:33,336 --> 00:56:36,533
-We should kill him before he...
-No!

756
00:56:39,075 --> 00:56:44,012
Never hate your enemies. it affects your judgement.

757
00:56:51,654 --> 00:56:56,717

758
00:56:59,562 --> 00:57:02,793
Nice to see you again, Mr Corleone.

759
00:57:22,552 --> 00:57:25,453
Hey, girls. Let's go.

760
00:57:42,939 --> 00:57:47,239
We trusted you to manage our money in the casinos.

761
00:57:47,343 --> 00:57:50,904
it's not even 20 years. You've sold the casinos

762
00:57:51,014 --> 00:57:53,107
and made fortunes for all of us.

763
00:57:53,216 --> 00:57:57,676
Bravo, Don Corleone!

764
00:57:57,787 --> 00:57:59,584
Thank you.

765
00:57:59,756 --> 00:58:03,283
Friends, I have come here

766
00:58:03,393 --> 00:58:07,853
because our business together is done.

767
00:58:08,331 --> 00:58:09,992
We have prospered,

768
00:58:10,099 --> 00:58:12,124
and now it is time for us

769
00:58:12,235 --> 00:58:15,864
to dissolve the business relationship between us.

770
00:58:17,407 --> 00:58:19,068
That's it.

771
00:58:19,175 --> 00:58:23,509
But I do have a little surprise. Al?

772
00:58:25,515 --> 00:58:28,211
Your shares in the casinos.

773
00:58:28,318 --> 00:58:32,049
I've cut the red tape, so you could get your money right away.

774
00:58:32,288 --> 00:58:33,915

775
00:58:34,257 --> 00:58:35,656

776
00:58:35,758 --> 00:58:36,782

777
00:58:38,661 --> 00:58:41,152
50 million dollars!

778
00:58:41,264 --> 00:58:46,930
-Not everybody gets the same. it depends on your investment.
-Nothing for you...

779
00:58:47,036 --> 00:58:50,164
Michael, this is really generous!

780
00:58:50,306 --> 00:58:52,831
Wonderful!

781
00:58:54,010 --> 00:58:55,534

782
00:58:55,645 --> 00:58:58,443
Parisi, how much did you invest?

783
00:58:58,715 --> 00:58:59,773
I don't remember.

784
00:58:59,849 --> 00:59:02,317
You're blessed.

785
00:59:07,423 --> 00:59:10,881
My family has done much of the hard work,

786
00:59:10,994 --> 00:59:13,360
taken many risks.

787
00:59:14,364 --> 00:59:18,528
All to make money for the rest of the families.

788
00:59:19,836 --> 00:59:22,771
You all know Joey Zasa.

789
00:59:22,872 --> 00:59:26,205
He is, I admit, an important man.

790
00:59:26,376 --> 00:59:30,676
His picture is on the cover of the New York Times magazine.

791
00:59:30,780 --> 00:59:35,911
He gets the Esquire Magazine award for the best dressed gangster.

792
00:59:36,019 --> 00:59:41,116
The newspapers praise him because he hires Blacks,

793
00:59:41,224 --> 00:59:43,351
which shows he has a good heart.

794
00:59:45,094 --> 00:59:49,258
He is famous. Who knows?

795
00:59:49,365 --> 00:59:51,230
Maybe one day

796
00:59:51,334 --> 00:59:54,599
he'll make all of you popular.

797
00:59:55,471 --> 00:59:56,631
it's true.

798
00:59:56,739 --> 01:00:00,573
I make more of a bella figura.

799
01:00:00,676 --> 01:00:02,439
That is my nature.

800
01:00:02,545 --> 01:00:07,505
But I also want to make a move into legitimate enterprises.

801
01:00:07,617 --> 01:00:10,085
I'd like a little pin from the Pope.

802
01:00:10,586 --> 01:00:13,453
Sure, I take the Blacks

803
01:00:13,556 --> 01:00:15,922
and the Spanish into my family,

804
01:00:16,025 --> 01:00:20,086
because that's America.

805
01:00:20,196 --> 01:00:25,224
And you guarantee that they don't deal drugs?

806
01:00:25,334 --> 01:00:27,359
I don't guarantee that.

807
01:00:27,470 --> 01:00:31,304
I guarantee that I'll kill anybody who does.

808
01:00:34,710 --> 01:00:37,975
Let me talk to him.

809
01:00:38,081 --> 01:00:40,276
Who can refuse Don Altobello?

810
01:00:40,383 --> 01:00:41,645
Joey, are you...

811
01:00:41,751 --> 01:00:43,275
No!

812
01:00:43,419 --> 01:00:44,545
I say to all of you:

813
01:00:44,687 --> 01:00:49,852
I have been treated this day with no respect.

814
01:00:49,959 --> 01:00:51,984
I've earned you all money.

815
01:00:52,095 --> 01:00:53,858
I've made you rich

816
01:00:53,963 --> 01:00:55,396
and I asked for little.

817
01:00:55,498 --> 01:00:58,092
Good. You will not give,

818
01:00:58,201 --> 01:01:00,601
so I'll take!

819
01:01:00,703 --> 01:01:03,467
As for Don Corleone,

820
01:01:03,573 --> 01:01:07,373
he makes it very clear to me today

821
01:01:07,477 --> 01:01:10,969
that he is my enemy.

822
01:01:13,249 --> 01:01:15,877
You must choose between us.

823
01:01:19,021 --> 01:01:24,015
No, Joey!

824
01:01:24,127 --> 01:01:27,426
Michael, we could reason together.

825
01:01:27,997 --> 01:01:31,763
No. Michael, please...

826
01:01:31,901 --> 01:01:33,334
