01:26:28,767 --> 01:26:30,564
could advise us.

1094
01:26:30,969 --> 01:26:35,030
What do you think about Altobello?

1095
01:26:37,175 --> 01:26:39,268
A very talented man.

1096
01:26:39,378 --> 01:26:40,936
He has kept the peace

1097
01:26:41,046 --> 01:26:44,209
between our Sicilian and American friends.

1098
01:26:44,316 --> 01:26:46,750
The saint of reason.

1099
01:26:48,887 --> 01:26:51,287
A blood bath in Atlantic City

1100
01:26:51,423 --> 01:26:53,015
left New York a mess.

1101
01:26:53,125 --> 01:26:56,424
Joey Zasa at least was running a tight ship,

1102
01:26:56,528 --> 01:27:00,396
but with him out of the picture we must step in.

1103
01:27:00,499 --> 01:27:02,194
Step back in...

1104
01:27:02,300 --> 01:27:03,324
Or the Chinese

1105
01:27:03,468 --> 01:27:04,992
and Colombians will.

1106
01:27:05,237 --> 01:27:07,262
The Corleones left drugs,

1107
01:27:07,372 --> 01:27:11,274
so New York is weak, and Palermo is strong.

1108
01:27:11,843 --> 01:27:13,640
Your enemies always get strong

1109
01:27:13,745 --> 01:27:15,838
on what you leave behind.

1110
01:27:16,314 --> 01:27:18,282

1111
01:27:18,517 --> 01:27:23,750
Who could give the order for that massacre...

1112
01:27:24,956 --> 01:27:29,120
and still pressure the Vatican deal?

1113
01:27:29,227 --> 01:27:31,058
Only Lucchesi

1114
01:27:31,163 --> 01:27:34,724
can reach between these two worlds.

1115
01:27:36,068 --> 01:27:39,560
"Our ships must all sail in the same direction"...

1116
01:27:41,073 --> 01:27:44,133
Italian politics have had these men for centuries.

1117
01:27:44,242 --> 01:27:47,006
They are the true Mafia.

1118
01:27:47,112 --> 01:27:50,309
The Archbishop and the Vatican Bank, that's the big problem.

1119
01:27:50,415 --> 01:27:52,110
They're the same problem.

1120
01:27:52,217 --> 01:27:55,186
B.J., they're connected.

1121
01:27:55,420 --> 01:27:58,480
The Archbishop has powerful friends.

1122
01:28:00,726 --> 01:28:02,591
They totally protect him.

1123
01:28:02,761 --> 01:28:07,562
Is there someone in the Church we can turn to?

1124
01:28:07,666 --> 01:28:09,861
Someone we can tell our problem to?

1125
01:28:12,237 --> 01:28:14,762
Cardinal Lamberto.

1126
01:28:14,873 --> 01:28:18,172
A wise and good man...

1127
01:28:18,276 --> 01:28:20,107
very influential.

1128
01:28:20,212 --> 01:28:24,114
He will see you.

1129
01:28:28,220 --> 01:28:30,916
I will see this Cardinal Lamberto

1130
01:28:31,022 --> 01:28:34,321
and see if we can work things out.

1131
01:28:35,827 --> 01:28:41,163
You honour your agreements, but you are dealing with crooks.

1132
01:28:41,266 --> 01:28:43,461
They have no honour.

1133
01:28:45,871 --> 01:28:47,634
My word is final.

1134
01:28:57,816 --> 01:29:02,276
Politics and crime, they're the same thing.

1135
01:29:18,503 --> 01:29:22,132

1136
01:29:24,376 --> 01:29:26,606
I've invited you all here

1137
01:29:26,711 --> 01:29:31,375
to celebrate my son's debut in an opera house...

1138
01:29:31,650 --> 01:29:35,677
We'll play "Philadelphia".

1139
01:29:35,787 --> 01:29:39,382
Seven cards. Two down, four up. Deuces and one-eyed jacks are wild.

1140
01:29:39,491 --> 01:29:41,789
...in the opera "Cavallaria Rusticana".

1141
01:29:41,893 --> 01:29:44,657
It's "Cavalleria Rusticana", Dad.

1142
01:29:44,763 --> 01:29:48,164
"Cavalleria". I think I have tickets to the wrong opera.

1143
01:29:48,733 --> 01:29:50,166
I've been in New York too long.

1144
01:29:50,268 --> 01:29:53,829
You will all receive tickets,

1145
01:29:53,939 --> 01:29:55,463
so come on time.

1146
01:29:55,607 --> 01:29:56,835
Dad, I've got a present for you.

1147
01:29:56,908 --> 01:29:57,897

1148
01:29:57,976 --> 01:29:59,136

1149
01:30:01,613 --> 01:30:03,945
it comes from the town of Corleone

1150
01:30:04,049 --> 01:30:05,949
and it's authentic Sicilian.

1151
01:30:09,154 --> 01:30:11,213
And... I learned it for you.

1152
01:31:40,078 --> 01:31:44,139
She was wonderful, beautiful. I loved her.

1153
01:31:44,249 --> 01:31:45,876
And then she died.

1154
01:31:46,618 --> 01:31:49,086
My trusted bodyguard

1155
01:31:50,021 --> 01:31:52,717
planted a bomb in my car.

1156
01:31:53,325 --> 01:31:55,350
She drove it before I did.

1157
01:31:57,062 --> 01:32:00,691
Why is such a beautiful country so violent?

1158
01:32:00,799 --> 01:32:02,289
History.

1159
01:32:02,400 --> 01:32:06,996
Mom was telling me about when your biggest worry was passing your exams.

1160
01:32:07,105 --> 01:32:08,970
Yes, it was then.

1161
01:32:09,107 --> 01:32:10,972
I worry about you now.

1162
01:32:11,076 --> 01:32:16,309
Oh, Mary, you're such a warm-hearted girl. You always were.

1163
01:32:16,414 --> 01:32:18,041
I love my family.

1164
01:32:18,450 --> 01:32:20,213
Even your cousin Vincent?

1165
01:32:23,722 --> 01:32:25,986
I really love him.

1166
01:32:27,359 --> 01:32:29,054
He's your first cousin.

1167
01:32:29,160 --> 01:32:31,128
Then I love him first.

1168
01:32:31,629 --> 01:32:35,065
Mary, you can't see him.

1169
01:32:35,166 --> 01:32:37,896
Just don't see him anymore.

1170
01:32:38,336 --> 01:32:42,568
He's right. it's too dangerous.

1171
01:32:44,109 --> 01:32:45,371
Mary,

1172
01:32:45,477 --> 01:32:48,742
you can't see him anymore. Not in that fashion.

1173
01:32:48,847 --> 01:32:50,178
No.

1174
01:32:51,316 --> 01:32:54,774
-Please, promise me.
-No!

1175
01:32:54,886 --> 01:32:56,148
Obey me on this.

1176
01:32:56,254 --> 01:32:57,949
No, Dad!

1177
01:33:02,494 --> 01:33:04,519
Mary is smart, Dad.

1178
01:33:05,163 --> 01:33:07,256
She'll understand eventually.

1179
01:33:29,821 --> 01:33:33,484
Bella cugina... Tesoro mio.

1180
01:33:44,202 --> 01:33:45,191
You wanted to see me?

1181
01:33:45,303 --> 01:33:46,736
Yeah.

1182
01:33:47,238 --> 01:33:49,536
I want you to do something for me.

1183
01:33:49,641 --> 01:33:51,074
it's dangerous.

1184
01:33:52,410 --> 01:33:56,312
Good. I'm in. What do you need?

1185
01:33:56,414 --> 01:33:59,315
I want you to sell your soul to Don Altobello.

1186
01:34:00,085 --> 01:34:01,746
To betray me.

1187
01:34:05,457 --> 01:34:07,049
He'd never believe me.

1188
01:34:08,426 --> 01:34:11,395
-That depends.
-Sit down.

1189
01:34:13,965 --> 01:34:15,523
I have an idea.

1190
01:34:17,001 --> 01:34:21,301
See if you can learn how high Altobello is connected.

1191
01:34:24,742 --> 01:34:27,176
Arrange a meeting.

1192
01:34:28,980 --> 01:34:32,006
You say how devoted you are to me.

1193
01:34:32,283 --> 01:34:34,547
Tell him your problems.

1194
01:34:34,652 --> 01:34:36,847
Ask for his help.

1195
01:34:36,955 --> 01:34:38,547
What problems?

1196
01:34:39,557 --> 01:34:42,117
That you want to run away with my daughter.

1197
01:34:42,994 --> 01:34:47,897
But you know that if you do, I will become your enemy.

1198
01:34:52,036 --> 01:34:54,266
You know that I would never do that.

1199
01:34:54,539 --> 01:34:56,029
I know.

1200
01:34:56,808 --> 01:35:02,075
Ask Altobello to speak to me. To further the marriage.

1201
01:35:02,180 --> 01:35:04,307
But you're cousins, after all.

1202
01:35:04,415 --> 01:35:07,782
Michael was always a little old-fashioned.

1203
01:35:07,919 --> 01:35:13,858
Say you can't belong to my legitimate world. That you want your own family.

1204
01:35:13,958 --> 01:35:15,983
I could straighten out what Joey Zasa left behind.

1205
01:35:18,630 --> 01:35:22,498
I could use your friendship to persuade him.

1206
01:35:22,600 --> 01:35:25,330
I would be indebted to you forever.

1207
01:35:27,372 --> 01:35:29,135
A Corleone

1208
01:35:29,340 --> 01:35:32,104
knows the value of such a friend.

1209
01:35:32,877 --> 01:35:35,675
Then you would work for me?

1210
01:35:36,347 --> 01:35:42,877
Si. Bacio la mano, Don Altobello.

1211
01:35:44,022 --> 01:35:45,683

1212
01:35:45,790 --> 01:35:49,783
if he hints that he wants you to betray me,

1213
01:35:49,928 --> 01:35:51,327
get insuited,

1214
01:35:51,462 --> 01:35:53,930
because that's his trap.

1215
01:36:00,405 --> 01:36:04,341
You're not telling me the whole truth, Vincenzo.

1216
01:36:06,744 --> 01:36:13,775
Isn't it true, that with Michael gone, the girl controls everything?

1217
01:36:16,521 --> 01:36:18,921
Leave the girl out of this.

1218
01:36:19,057 --> 01:36:22,823
Of course, you love her. And she loves you.

1219
01:36:42,947 --> 01:36:46,815
I guessed it, didn't I?

1220
01:36:47,352 --> 01:36:50,480
You're a wise man, Don Altobello.

1221
01:36:50,622 --> 01:36:53,318
I'll be learning a lot from you.

1222
01:36:53,424 --> 01:36:57,793
The richest man is the one with the most powerful friends.

1223
01:36:59,397 --> 01:37:03,299
it's my duty to make the introductions.

1224
01:37:09,007 --> 01:37:10,838
Don Lucchesi.

1225
01:37:13,745 --> 01:37:18,148
Don Altobello tells me that you have a strong character.

1226
01:37:18,249 --> 01:37:19,580
A man of respect.

1227
01:37:19,684 --> 01:37:23,381
This is the hero who put Joey Zasa in his grave.

1228
01:37:23,488 --> 01:37:25,080
if we'd known of his existence,

1229
01:37:25,189 --> 01:37:27,817
we wouldn't have backed Joey.

1230
01:37:27,925 --> 01:37:30,223
No one wants another Joe.

1231
01:37:31,896 --> 01:37:34,694
Let me be your friend.

1232
01:37:34,799 --> 01:37:37,734
Even the strongest man needs friends.

1233
01:37:37,835 --> 01:37:39,359
I'm flattered.

1234
01:37:40,405 --> 01:37:43,238
You're a man of finance and politics.

1235
01:37:43,341 --> 01:37:45,468
Things I don't understand.

1236
01:37:46,577 --> 01:37:48,841
You understand guns.

1237
01:37:48,946 --> 01:37:51,312
Finance is a gun.

1238
01:37:51,416 --> 01:37:53,316
Politics...

1239
01:37:53,484 --> 01:37:56,942
is knowing when to pull the trigger.

1240
01:38:00,191 --> 01:38:01,886
How can I help?

1241
01:38:06,964 --> 01:38:09,728
Blessed is the peacemaker,

1242
01:38:09,834 --> 01:38:12,860
for he can be called the child of God.

1243
01:38:12,970 --> 01:38:17,339
-Tu parli Italiano un poco?
-Si.

1244
01:38:38,296 --> 01:38:40,730
The wheelchair, for Don Tommasino.

1245
01:38:48,873 --> 01:38:52,434
I trusted this business arrangement with the Archbishop.

1246
01:38:52,543 --> 01:38:57,674
I trusted him. I was sure his honesty was beyond a doubt.

1247
01:38:57,782 --> 01:39:02,981
But, as you see, I'm now the victim of a swindle.

1248
01:39:03,087 --> 01:39:04,952
He's stalling me.

1249
01:39:05,089 --> 01:39:09,082
Vast monies have gone to people in high political places

1250
01:39:09,193 --> 01:39:12,060
and the Vatican Bank is the guarantor.

1251
01:39:12,163 --> 01:39:14,757
if what you say is true,

1252
01:39:14,866 --> 01:39:18,063
there will be a great scandal.

1253
01:39:19,637 --> 01:39:21,127
Look at this stone.

1254
01:39:21,239 --> 01:39:24,538
it has been in the water for a very long time,

1255
01:39:24,642 --> 01:39:29,272
but the water has not penetrated it.

1256
01:39:32,350 --> 01:39:33,783
Look...

1257
01:39:34,719 --> 01:39:36,949
Perfectly dry.

1258
01:39:37,522 --> 01:39:40,047
The same thing has happened to men in Europe.

1259
01:39:40,158 --> 01:39:44,959
For centuries they have been surrounded by Christianity,

1260
01:39:45,062 --> 01:39:47,792
but Christ has not penetrated.

1261
01:39:47,899 --> 01:39:52,233
Christ doesn't live within them.

1262
01:39:54,839 --> 01:39:55,897
What's happening?

1263
01:39:55,973 --> 01:40:00,273
Could you get me something sweet?

1264
01:40:00,378 --> 01:40:03,313
Some orange juice, candy...

1265
01:40:06,484 --> 01:40:09,419
I have trouble with diabetes.

1266
01:40:12,423 --> 01:40:14,891
My blood sugar goes low.

1267
01:40:15,026 --> 01:40:17,358
I understand.

1268
01:40:39,750 --> 01:40:42,719
it happens sometimes when I'm under stress.

1269
01:40:43,554 --> 01:40:45,351
I understand.

1270
01:40:47,158 --> 01:40:49,149
To come to you

1271
01:40:49,527 --> 01:40:52,223
on such a delicate matter...

1272
01:40:53,865 --> 01:40:57,198
Accusations against your Archbishop.

1273
01:40:57,301 --> 01:40:59,929
it was difficuit for me.

1274
01:41:00,137 --> 01:41:02,230
The mind suffers

1275
01:41:02,406 --> 01:41:06,240
and the body cries out.

1276
01:41:09,146 --> 01:41:13,776
That's true.

1277
01:41:14,619 --> 01:41:19,386
Would you like to make your confession?

1278
01:41:25,429 --> 01:41:27,397
Your Eminence,

1279
01:41:27,965 --> 01:41:33,631
I'm... it's been so long.

1280
01:41:33,738 --> 01:41:38,141
I wouldn't... I wouldn't know where to...

1281
01:41:38,242 --> 01:41:41,268
it's been 30 years.

1282
01:41:41,612 --> 01:41:45,605
I'd use up too much of your time, I think.

1283
01:41:45,716 --> 01:41:49,447
I always have time to save souls.

1284
01:41:51,155 --> 01:41:53,783
Well, I'm beyond redemption.

1285
01:41:53,925 --> 01:41:56,155
No, no...

1286
01:42:03,868 --> 01:42:08,771
I hear the confessions of my own priests here.

1287
01:42:08,873 --> 01:42:13,105
Sometimes the desire to confess is overwhelming,

1288
01:42:13,210 --> 01:42:16,077
and we must seize the moment.

1289
01:42:20,184 --> 01:42:22,482
What is the point of confessing

1290
01:42:22,587 --> 01:42:24,782
if I don't repent?

1291
01:42:26,390 --> 01:42:29,757
I hear you are a practical man.

1292
01:42:29,860 --> 01:42:33,091
What have you got to lose?

1293
01:42:43,708 --> 01:42:45,403
Go on.

1294
01:42:51,949 --> 01:42:54,144
I...

1295
01:42:54,485 --> 01:42:56,783
...betrayed my wife.

1296
01:42:58,055 --> 01:43:00,250
Go on, my son.

1297
01:43:05,363 --> 01:43:07,354
I betrayed myself.

1298
01:43:10,101 --> 01:43:11,966
I killed men.

1299
01:43:15,806 --> 01:43:18,400
And I ordered men to be killed.

1300
01:43:19,710 --> 01:43:23,077
Go on, my son. Go on.

1301
01:43:27,084 --> 01:43:29,609
it's useless.

1302
01:43:31,155 --> 01:43:33,521
Go on, my son.

1303
01:43:34,525 --> 01:43:36,322
I killed...

1304
01:43:40,731 --> 01:43:44,030
I ordered the death of my brother.

1305
01:43:44,468 --> 01:43:47,130
He injured me.

1306
01:43:47,872 --> 01:43:51,330
I killed my mother's son.

1307
01:43:51,776 --> 01:43:55,576
I killed my father's son.

1308
01:44:04,522 --> 01:44:06,786
Your sins are terrible,

1309
01:44:06,891 --> 01:44:10,554
and it is just that you suffer.

1310
01:44:10,695 --> 01:44:14,153
Your life could be redeemed,

1311
01:44:14,265 --> 01:44:16,460
but I know that you don't believe that.

1312
01:44:16,567 --> 01:44:18,660
You will not change.

1313
01:44:41,926 --> 01:44:45,157
the Supreme Pontiff of the Roman Catholic Church,...

1314
01:44:45,262 --> 01:44:50,723
Pope Paul Vl,

1315
01:44:50,835 --> 01:44:54,965
died last night at 9:40 p.m.

1316
01:44:55,072 --> 01:44:59,065
The Pope was 81 years old,...

1317
01:44:59,176 --> 01:45:04,944
and had been in poor health for the last several months.

1318
01:45:10,454 --> 01:45:11,921
Connie...

1319
01:45:13,691 --> 01:45:18,788
All my life I've kept trying to go up in society.

1320
01:45:18,929 --> 01:45:22,922
To where everything higher up was legal, straight...

1321
01:45:23,701 --> 01:45:28,035
But the higher I go, the more crooked it becomes.

1322
01:45:29,974 --> 01:45:32,204
Where the hell does it end?

1323
01:45:41,285 --> 01:45:44,584
They've been killing each other for centuries here.

1324
01:45:45,956 --> 01:45:47,685
For money,

1325
01:45:47,825 --> 01:45:51,488
for pride, for family.

1326
01:45:53,297 --> 01:45:58,030
To keep from becoming the slaves of the rich pezzi da novanta.

1327
01:46:04,508 --> 01:46:07,136
I made confession, Connie.

1328
01:46:07,645 --> 01:46:10,512
I confessed my sins.

1329
01:46:11,382 --> 01:46:13,976
Why? That's not like you.

1330
01:46:14,084 --> 01:46:17,451
You don't have to confess your sins to a stranger.

1331
01:46:17,555 --> 01:46:19,420
it was the man.

1332
01:46:20,257 --> 01:46:22,384
He's a good man.

1333
01:46:22,560 --> 01:46:24,528
A true priest.

1334
01:46:27,932 --> 01:46:30,025
He can change things.

1335
01:46:32,436 --> 01:46:34,427
Michael...

1336
01:46:35,306 --> 01:46:37,171
You know,

1337
01:46:37,274 --> 01:46:40,107
sometimes I think of poor Fredo.

1338
01:46:40,211 --> 01:46:42,577
Drowned.

1339
01:46:42,680 --> 01:46:44,477
it was God's will.

1340
01:46:46,016 --> 01:46:48,610
it was a terrible accident.

1341
01:46:49,553 --> 01:46:51,783
But it's finished.

1342
01:46:56,794 --> 01:46:58,955
Michael, I love you.

1343
01:47:00,831 --> 01:47:03,994
I'll always help you.

1344
01:47:15,212 --> 01:47:17,237
Oh, Connie...

1345
01:47:46,677 --> 01:47:49,407
I am honored, Don Altobello,

1346
01:47:49,513 --> 01:47:54,143
that you've come from Palermo to visit me.

1347
01:47:58,088 --> 01:48:02,616
Hey, the little kid! He's grown.

1348
01:48:02,760 --> 01:48:05,285
Do the donkey for me.

1349
01:48:21,946 --> 01:48:24,414
it's been some time

1350
01:48:24,515 --> 01:48:27,382
since we did business together.

1351
01:48:29,853 --> 01:48:31,286
You are my "ace in the hole,"

1352
01:48:31,388 --> 01:48:34,687
as we say in America.

1353
01:48:35,092 --> 01:48:38,289
I have a stone in my shoe.

1354
01:48:38,395 --> 01:48:41,694
You can remove it.

1355
01:48:48,172 --> 01:48:50,606
Only one stone?

1356
01:48:53,277 --> 01:48:56,838
it's dangerous.

1357
01:48:56,981 --> 01:48:59,006
A famous man.

1358
01:48:59,116 --> 01:49:03,610
You will have to take precautions.

1359
01:49:05,489 --> 01:49:08,117
Tell me what to do.

1360
01:49:08,225 --> 01:49:11,752
Then I will tell you my price.

1361
01:49:16,266 --> 01:49:18,461
Ah, what bread!

1362
01:49:22,172 --> 01:49:24,663
Olive oil...

1363
01:49:29,580 --> 01:49:31,070
Virgin...

1364
01:49:31,181 --> 01:49:33,547
only in Sicily.

1365
01:49:35,686 --> 01:49:37,278
Alla salute!

1366
01:49:37,388 --> 01:49:39,356
To death.

1367
01:49:53,170 --> 01:49:54,501
kay!

1368
01:49:54,938 --> 01:49:56,701
-Connie!
-How are you?

1369
01:49:57,174 --> 01:49:59,608
Mary, I've missed you.

1370
01:50:00,778 --> 01:50:02,837
Hello, Michael.

1371
01:50:02,946 --> 01:50:04,743
Mom, look at this.

1372
01:50:04,848 --> 01:50:08,409

1373
01:50:08,552 --> 01:50:10,679
it's too bad Douglas couldn't come.

1374
01:50:10,788 --> 01:50:14,588
I know. He had a very important trial.

1375
01:50:14,725 --> 01:50:16,750
I know he wanted to come.

1376
01:50:17,926 --> 01:50:20,224
-The car is...
-Okay.

1377
01:50:21,799 --> 01:50:25,758
Well, your son is an artist.

1378
01:50:25,869 --> 01:50:28,394
Oh, yes. Thanks to you.

1379
01:50:28,572 --> 01:50:30,005
What for?

1380
01:50:30,607 --> 01:50:33,167
For making me let him go.

1381
01:50:33,744 --> 01:50:35,109
Well,

1382
01:50:35,212 --> 01:50:36,611
after all these years,

1383
01:50:36,713 --> 01:50:38,840
here I am in Sicily for the first time.

1384
01:50:38,949 --> 01:50:41,076
-I want to get a picture of you together.
-Okay.

1385
01:50:44,121 --> 01:50:45,884
Hey, Dad. Smile!

1386
01:50:50,327 --> 01:50:53,956
I see you still have Al Neri. Why?

1387
01:50:54,465 --> 01:50:58,526
I need him. He helps me get in and out of the car.

1388
01:50:59,169 --> 01:51:00,932
He carries my briefcase.

1389
01:51:01,271 --> 01:51:03,296
You're still a liar, Michael.

1390
01:51:04,441 --> 01:51:07,842
Let me show you Sicily, the real Sicily.

1391
01:51:07,945 --> 01:51:10,436
So you'll understand the family history.

1392
01:51:10,547 --> 01:51:13,175
I think I understand it more than enough.

1393
01:51:42,379 --> 01:51:44,006

1394
01:52:05,068 --> 01:52:06,626
Anthony,

1395
01:52:06,737 --> 01:52:12,073
I have something you made for me a very long time ago.

1396
01:52:12,776 --> 01:52:15,074
-Might bring you luck.
-Thanks.

1397
01:52:19,583 --> 01:52:21,050
You saved it...

1398
01:52:21,185 --> 01:52:23,085
I remember.

1399
01:52:27,057 --> 01:52:28,581
Thank you, Dad.

1400
01:52:30,427 --> 01:52:31,951
I'm proud of you.

1401
01:52:32,829 --> 01:52:34,091
Thank you.

1402
01:52:50,447 --> 01:52:52,506
Are they as good as they look?

1403
01:52:52,616 --> 01:52:55,642
Better. They're the best.

1404
01:52:55,986 --> 01:52:58,477
As long as they are around, Uncle Michael is safe.

1405
01:52:58,589 --> 01:53:00,682
Goodbye.

1406
01:53:02,726 --> 01:53:04,318
Tell your father I'll be back for dinner.

1407
01:53:04,428 --> 01:53:05,395
Okay.

1408
01:53:06,263 --> 01:53:07,321
Have fun.

1409
01:53:07,397 --> 01:53:09,024
Tell Tony to wait for me.

1410
01:53:09,132 --> 01:53:10,724
I will.

1411
01:53:11,969 --> 01:53:13,027

1412
01:53:13,103 --> 01:53:16,834
Buongiorno, signora. At your service.

1413
01:53:20,744 --> 01:53:23,941
if I see Dad, I'll tell him you left.

1414
01:53:28,986 --> 01:53:33,423
You're the only one left with my father's strength.

1415
01:53:34,825 --> 01:53:38,727
if anything happens to Michael, I want you to strike back.

1416
01:53:41,865 --> 01:53:44,595
I'll have everything ready.

1417
01:53:47,337 --> 01:53:48,998
Do you swear?

1418
01:53:56,480 --> 01:53:58,072
I swear to you.

1419
01:54:28,512 --> 01:54:34,644
Here it is. The house where my father was born.

1420
01:54:35,585 --> 01:54:37,576
This is where they came

1421
01:54:37,688 --> 01:54:42,182
to take him when he was a boy. To kill him.

1422
01:54:44,227 --> 01:54:45,922
Wait...

1423
01:54:46,697 --> 01:54:48,392
Listen to that.

1424
01:55:07,818 --> 01:55:10,184
You know Mary's in love.

1425
01:55:11,288 --> 01:55:12,915
Yes, I know.

1426
01:55:14,124 --> 01:55:18,857
With a handsome young Italian man with dark eyes...

1427
01:55:19,429 --> 01:55:21,329
I won't allow it.

1428
01:55:23,967 --> 01:55:25,400
it's wrong.

1429
01:55:25,736 --> 01:55:28,034
it's wrong and it's dangerous.

1430
01:55:28,171 --> 01:55:31,231
"Oh father, my father!"

1431
01:55:31,341 --> 01:55:34,139
"Give me some time to pray to the Lord."

1432
01:55:34,244 --> 01:55:37,475
The Baroness of Carini had betrayed her husband...

1433
01:55:37,681 --> 01:55:41,845
and fallen in love with her cousin.

1434
01:55:41,952 --> 01:55:45,444
"There will be no forgiveness!"

1435
01:55:46,456 --> 01:55:48,754
Her father stabbed her

1436
01:55:48,859 --> 01:55:52,920
through the heart.

1437
01:56:00,103 --> 01:56:01,661
Honour, huh?

1438
01:56:21,324 --> 01:56:24,452
I remember the time you came to my parents' house

1439
01:56:24,561 --> 01:56:28,463
and told me about the family business.

1440
01:56:28,565 --> 01:56:31,295
How you'd never have anything to do with it.

1441
01:56:31,468 --> 01:56:33,902
You sounded like Tony.

1442
01:56:34,104 --> 01:56:36,129
I was a lot like Tony.

1443
01:56:43,812 --> 01:56:44,938
I can barely see him...

1444
01:56:45,015 --> 01:56:46,277
-kay?
-What?

1445
01:56:46,683 --> 01:56:47,741
Do you mind driving?

1446
01:56:47,818 --> 01:56:49,080
What's wrong?

1447
01:56:49,252 --> 01:56:52,085
My eyes. Sometimes they're all right, but...

1448
01:56:54,090 --> 01:56:55,819
I have to see Don Tommasino...

1449
01:56:55,926 --> 01:56:57,257

1450
01:57:00,262 --> 01:57:02,628
Well...

1451
01:57:02,632 --> 01:57:04,395
There are no bodyguards today.

1452
01:57:04,668 --> 01:57:06,260
I really snuck away.

1453
01:57:13,376 --> 01:57:20,578
Father, where are you going? Would you like a ride?

1454
01:57:27,357 --> 01:57:29,552
I know you.

1455
01:57:29,659 --> 01:57:32,253
You're Mosca of Montelepre.

1456
01:57:32,362 --> 01:57:33,989
You were an assassin then,

1457
01:57:34,097 --> 01:57:36,190
and you're an assassin now.

1458
01:57:36,299 --> 01:57:40,235
I know Michael Corleone is at your house.

1459
01:57:40,337 --> 01:57:42,328
I will pass through the gates with you.

1460
01:57:59,422 --> 01:58:00,582
How are you?

1461
01:58:00,924 --> 01:58:04,519
This is Calo, one of my bodyguards in the old days.

1462
01:58:10,333 --> 01:58:12,733
-We can wait here.
-You want a drink?

1463
01:58:12,869 --> 01:58:14,166

1464
01:58:18,341 --> 01:58:21,037
I spent a lot of time in this room...

1465
01:58:22,412 --> 01:58:24,175
...thinking of you.

1466
01:58:27,484 --> 01:58:29,008
And then you got married.

1467
01:58:33,323 --> 01:58:34,881
I still thought of you.

1468
01:58:35,725 --> 01:58:37,352
What's in that room?

1469
01:58:41,431 --> 01:58:43,865
This is dangerous for you.

1470
01:58:43,967 --> 01:58:45,662
This is Sicily.

1471
01:58:48,038 --> 01:58:49,471
I love this country.

1472
01:58:49,573 --> 01:58:51,097
Why?

1473
01:58:53,043 --> 01:58:56,535
Well, all through history,

1474
01:58:56,646 --> 01:58:59,809
terrible things have happened to these people.

1475
01:58:59,916 --> 01:59:02,646
Terrible injustices.

1476
01:59:03,186 --> 01:59:06,212
But they still expect good,

1477
01:59:06,323 --> 01:59:08,518
rather than bad, will happen to them.

1478
01:59:08,625 --> 01:59:10,786
Sort of like me and you?

1479
01:59:14,698 --> 01:59:15,756
How so?

1480
01:59:15,832 --> 01:59:17,527
I'm still here, right?

1481
01:59:18,301 --> 01:59:20,496
We do have a bad history,

1482
01:59:20,604 --> 01:59:21,730
but I'm still here.

1483
01:59:21,838 --> 01:59:24,739
Yes, you are, but with dread.

1484
01:59:29,112 --> 01:59:31,342
Give me the order!

1485
01:59:31,448 --> 01:59:34,611
Is that supposed to make me not dread you?

1486
01:59:36,886 --> 01:59:39,184
We're in Sicily. it's opera.

1487
01:59:41,591 --> 01:59:42,853
Okay.

1488
01:59:45,495 --> 01:59:47,486
What do we do now?

1489
01:59:50,233 --> 01:59:51,928
Be reasonable.

1490
01:59:52,802 --> 01:59:54,667
Let's try not to hurt each other.

1491
02:00:01,778 --> 02:00:03,871
I want you to forgive me.

1492
02:00:06,683 --> 02:00:08,310
For what?

1493
02:00:08,918 --> 02:00:10,613
Everything.

1494
02:00:13,423 --> 02:00:16,790
Oh, like God?

1495
02:00:17,227 --> 02:00:20,788
No, I need something a little closer.

1496
02:00:22,832 --> 02:00:27,064
You couldn't understand, back in those days.

1497
02:00:27,504 --> 02:00:29,529
I loved my father.

1498
02:00:29,639 --> 02:00:32,506
I swore I would never be a man like him,

1499
02:00:32,609 --> 02:00:35,305
but I loved him and he was in danger.

1500
02:00:35,412 --> 02:00:36,902
What could I do?

1501
02:00:37,013 --> 02:00:40,471
And then later, you were in danger.

1502
02:00:40,583 --> 02:00:44,314
Our children were in danger. What could I do?

1503
02:00:44,921 --> 02:00:51,690
You were all that I... loved and valued most in the world.

1504
02:00:52,662 --> 02:00:55,859
Now I'm losing you. I lost you.

1505
02:00:55,965 --> 02:00:57,899
You're gone.

1506
02:00:58,968 --> 02:01:01,163
And it was all for nothing.

1507
02:01:01,304 --> 02:01:03,272
So...

1508
02:01:06,543 --> 02:01:12,379
You have to understand, I had a whole different destiny planned.

1509
02:01:15,218 --> 02:01:16,981
All right, I'll stop.

1510
02:01:27,597 --> 02:01:29,531
I really don't know what you want from me, Michael.

1511
02:01:29,632 --> 02:01:31,600

1512
02:01:32,001 --> 02:01:33,628
I mean...

1513
02:01:33,803 --> 02:01:37,330
I'm not the man that you think I am.

1514
02:01:37,974 --> 02:01:40,238
I don't know.

1515
02:01:40,343 --> 02:01:42,277
I love you, kay.

1516
02:01:43,279 --> 02:01:46,715
Don't dread me anymore.

1517
02:01:51,087 --> 02:01:56,855
You know, every night here in Sicily...

1518
02:01:57,060 --> 02:01:59,153
...I dream

1519
02:02:00,130 --> 02:02:03,258
about my wife and my children...

1520
02:02:05,769 --> 02:02:08,704
...and how I lost them.

1521
02:02:09,873 --> 02:02:16,676
I guess that if it's any consolation, I want you to know that...

1522
02:02:19,115 --> 02:02:24,382
that... I always loved you, Michael.

1523
02:02:25,321 --> 02:02:32,784
And you know... always, I always will.

1524
02:02:59,455 --> 02:03:00,945
What is it? What's wrong?

1525
02:03:02,392 --> 02:03:06,658
They found Don Tommasino shot.

1526
02:03:06,830 --> 02:03:08,354
Is he dead?

1527
02:03:10,667 --> 02:03:14,569
My master is dead. Blood calls for blood.

1528
02:03:14,704 --> 02:03:19,141
I must have revenge!

1529
02:03:21,010 --> 02:03:26,846
Some day, you may have to do a difficuit service for me.

1530
02:03:26,950 --> 02:03:30,408
- Command me.
- It never ends.

1531
02:03:31,554 --> 02:03:34,648
I will avenge him!

1532
02:03:48,838 --> 02:03:50,533
Totals...

1533
02:03:52,375 --> 02:03:55,344
Lorscheider, 1 vote.

1534
02:03:55,678 --> 02:03:59,170
Siri, 11 votes.

1535
02:03:59,282 --> 02:04:03,343
Lamberto, 99 votes.

1536
02:04:08,157 --> 02:04:11,524
Do you accept your election

1537
02:04:11,628 --> 02:04:13,960
as supreme pontiff?

1538
02:04:14,097 --> 02:04:20,127
Oh God, shed light on the decision they have taken on my behaif.

1539
02:04:20,503 --> 02:04:22,334
I accept.

1540
02:04:22,505 --> 02:04:25,030
By what name do you wish to be called?

1541
02:04:25,141 --> 02:04:28,599
John Paul the First.

1542
02:04:58,274 --> 02:05:00,367
I will do things "right away,"

1543
02:05:00,476 --> 02:05:04,640
rather than in "a little while"...

1544
02:05:04,781 --> 02:05:12,017
Frederick keinszig, known as "God's Banker", has been reported missing.

1545
02:05:12,155 --> 02:05:17,457
He was last seen leaving the Rome offices of Vatican owned Immobiliare.

1546
02:05:17,593 --> 02:05:21,393
Also missing was a large sum of money and several documents.

1547
02:05:21,497 --> 02:05:26,161
keinszig, you fool.

1548
02:05:28,104 --> 02:05:30,072
His absence casts

1549
02:05:30,173 --> 02:05:33,074
further suspicion on the dealings of the Vatican Bank.

1550
02:05:33,176 --> 02:05:36,043
For several years, the bank and its companies

1551
02:05:36,145 --> 02:05:41,742
have been the object of allegations of disreputable business practices.

1552
02:05:41,851 --> 02:05:46,220
Lucchesi, will you please try to understand?

1553
02:05:47,156 --> 02:05:48,919
I have phoned him.

1554
02:05:49,025 --> 02:05:51,357
I have waited here by the phone.

1555
02:05:54,464 --> 02:05:58,423
You would do well to remember, Mr Lucchesi,

1556
02:05:58,534 --> 02:06:01,002
that this Pope

1557
02:06:01,104 --> 02:06:06,098
has very different ideas from the last one.

1558
02:06:27,397 --> 02:06:29,729
Goodbye, my old friend.

1559
02:06:32,001 --> 02:06:34,367
You could have lived a little longer.

1560
02:06:35,638 --> 02:06:38,869
I could be closer to my dream.

1561
02:06:44,380 --> 02:06:47,281
You were so loved, Don Tommasino.

1562
02:06:51,888 --> 02:06:54,288
Why was I so feared,

1563
02:06:54,390 --> 02:06:56,517
and you so loved?

1564
02:06:56,893 --> 02:06:58,724
What was it?

1565
02:06:59,529 --> 02:07:02,020
I was no less honourable.

1566
02:07:03,766 --> 02:07:06,462
I wanted to do good.

1567
02:07:09,972 --> 02:07:11,166
What betrayed me?

1568
02:07:11,274 --> 02:07:14,107
My mind? My heart?

1569
02:07:15,878 --> 02:07:19,041
Why do I condemn myself so?

1570
02:07:24,954 --> 02:07:26,979
I swear,

1571
02:07:27,156 --> 02:07:30,250
on the lives of my children...

1572
02:07:33,896 --> 02:07:37,957
Give me a chance to redeem myself...

1573
02:07:40,603 --> 02:07:45,097
...and I will sin no more.

1574
02:08:08,364 --> 02:08:11,231
You look pale. Bad news?

1575
02:08:11,334 --> 02:08:12,858
Tell me right away.

1576
02:08:14,303 --> 02:08:16,771
it's not just a bad banking deal.

1577
02:08:18,040 --> 02:08:20,065
These guys are butchers.

1578
02:08:21,177 --> 02:08:23,042
What guys?

1579
02:08:23,146 --> 02:08:24,807
Lucchesi.

1580
02:08:25,681 --> 02:08:27,114
He controls all of them:

1581
02:08:27,216 --> 02:08:28,774
Altobello,

1582
02:08:28,885 --> 02:08:30,785
the Archbishop...

1583
02:08:31,420 --> 02:08:34,253
...others higher up, P2 maybe.

1584
02:08:34,390 --> 02:08:36,290
Secret unknown.

1585
02:08:36,425 --> 02:08:38,325
They're running things.

1586
02:08:41,030 --> 02:08:42,463
I'm in their way.

1587
02:08:43,833 --> 02:08:46,358
He's hired an assassin to kill you.

1588
02:08:46,469 --> 02:08:47,959
A Sicilian.

1589
02:08:48,070 --> 02:08:49,833
I don't know his name.

1590
02:08:51,140 --> 02:08:53,165
But they say he never fails.

1591
02:08:54,610 --> 02:08:56,635
Then no one is safe.

1592
02:08:59,549 --> 02:09:02,575
Even the new Pope is in danger.

1593
02:09:03,219 --> 02:09:07,451
We still have time. We can prevent this.

1594
02:09:11,460 --> 02:09:13,121
I tried, Vincent.

1595
02:09:15,932 --> 02:09:17,957
I tried...

1596
02:09:19,001 --> 02:09:21,902
...to keep everything from coming to this.

1597
02:09:22,138 --> 02:09:24,766
But it's not possible.

1598
02:09:24,874 --> 02:09:27,843
Not in this world.

1599
02:09:28,177 --> 02:09:30,372
Give me the order.

1600
02:09:33,683 --> 02:09:35,742
You won't be able to go back.

1601
02:09:37,019 --> 02:09:38,543
You'll be like me.

1602
02:09:38,688 --> 02:09:40,246
Good.

1603
02:09:40,923 --> 02:09:43,619
All my life I wanted out.

1604
02:09:43,793 --> 02:09:47,024
I wanted the family out.

1605
02:09:47,930 --> 02:09:50,262
I don't want out.

1606
02:09:50,399 --> 02:09:53,027
I want the power to preserve the family.

1607
02:09:57,740 --> 02:10:00,334
I'm asking for the order.

1608
02:10:20,830 --> 02:10:22,491
it's done.

1609
02:10:24,133 --> 02:10:26,829
Because I can't do it anymore.

1610
02:10:31,240 --> 02:10:32,605
Well, it doesn't matter.

1611
02:10:32,708 --> 02:10:36,007
Vincent knows what to do. Come on outside.

1612
02:10:36,112 --> 02:10:39,639
Take a rest and don't think about it.

1613
02:10:39,749 --> 02:10:41,239
All I do is think about it.

1614
02:10:41,350 --> 02:10:43,113
I'm your son.

1615
02:10:43,786 --> 02:10:46,118
Command me in all things.

1616
02:10:48,124 --> 02:10:50,524
Give up my daughter.

1617
02:10:53,062 --> 02:10:55,189
That's the price you pay...

1618
02:10:56,365 --> 02:10:58,663
...for the life you choose.

1619
02:11:24,927 --> 02:11:26,417
Nephew...

1620
02:11:28,664 --> 02:11:30,928
...from this moment on...

1621
02:11:32,401 --> 02:11:34,995
...call yourself Vincent Corleone.

1622
02:11:39,775 --> 02:11:42,835
Sit.

1623
02:11:56,225 --> 02:11:57,954
Don Vincenzo...

1624
02:12:00,062 --> 02:12:01,757

1625
02:12:03,699 --> 02:12:05,564
Don Corleone...

1626
02:12:08,871 --> 02:12:11,567
Don Vincenzo Corleone...

1627
02:12:59,889 --> 02:13:01,083

1628
02:13:24,413 --> 02:13:26,779

1629
02:13:44,733 --> 02:13:47,133
E tu, Vincenzo...

1630
02:13:47,269 --> 02:13:50,136
I know how you feel about Michael,

1631
02:13:50,239 --> 02:13:52,469
but you can't save him.

1632
02:13:52,708 --> 02:13:54,608
He's lost.

1633
02:13:55,678 --> 02:13:57,976
Think of yourself.

1634
02:13:58,647 --> 02:14:01,275
What's your answer, Vincent?

1635
02:14:03,085 --> 02:14:05,451
Enjoy the opera.

1636
02:14:06,956 --> 02:14:08,947
it's all taken care of.

1637
02:14:14,363 --> 02:14:16,888
Check the bar. I'll check the top floor.

1638
02:14:20,970 --> 02:14:23,962
"Here's hoping Tony sings better at the Teatro Massimo

1639
02:14:24,106 --> 02:14:25,573
than in the shower."

1640
02:14:25,539 --> 02:14:27,564
"Love, Douglas."

1641
02:14:27,843 --> 02:14:30,175
My darling Constanza!

1642
02:14:30,479 --> 02:14:32,174
Don Altobello.

1643
02:14:32,281 --> 02:14:33,942
This is a great occasion.

1644
02:14:34,049 --> 02:14:35,676
Come, sit down.

1645
02:14:39,755 --> 02:14:41,620
Happy birthday.

1646
02:14:42,024 --> 02:14:44,492
You're 80, but don't look more than 60.

1647
02:14:44,593 --> 02:14:46,754
You're the only one who remembered.

1648
02:14:46,862 --> 02:14:50,491
We've just got the word. The Pope has ratified the Immobiliare deal.

1649
02:14:50,599 --> 02:14:51,861
We've won.

1650
02:14:52,067 --> 02:14:53,728
Congratulations.

1651
02:14:56,705 --> 02:14:59,105
Strange how things work.

1652
02:14:59,208 --> 02:15:00,937
The Pope is doing what you said he'd do.

1653
02:15:01,043 --> 02:15:02,510
He's cleaning house.

1654
02:15:03,679 --> 02:15:05,909
He should be careful.

1655
02:15:06,081 --> 02:15:07,776
it's dangerous to be an honest man.

1656
02:15:14,557 --> 02:15:17,287
I want to put more muscle backstage with Tony.

1657
02:15:29,505 --> 02:15:32,838
On your birthday you used to shower me with treats.

1658
02:15:32,975 --> 02:15:34,533
Tootsie Rolls!

1659
02:15:35,644 --> 02:15:39,102
The nuns who made this cannoli took a vow of silence.

1660
02:15:39,214 --> 02:15:41,045
They're the very finest.

1661
02:15:46,822 --> 02:15:48,289
Hey, cous.

1662
02:15:51,493 --> 02:15:53,051
Where's your leather?

1663
02:15:56,432 --> 02:15:57,899
Stop it.

1664
02:16:03,906 --> 02:16:08,240
You're so thin. You eat it.

1665
02:16:23,859 --> 02:16:29,661
E buono. Grazie!

1666
02:16:31,000 --> 02:16:32,331
it's over.

1667
02:16:32,434 --> 02:16:35,403
There are things I have to do that you can't be part of.

1668
02:16:35,504 --> 02:16:39,838
it's not your father's decision, it's mine.

1669
02:16:40,175 --> 02:16:42,234
Don't hate your father.

1670
02:16:44,613 --> 02:16:49,107
There are things I'll be part of that you can't be around.

1671
02:16:50,185 --> 02:16:53,313
After tonight, you won't see me anymore.

1672
02:16:53,856 --> 02:16:55,551

1673
02:16:57,359 --> 02:17:00,886
You've got to understand, Mary. You've got to understand.

1674
02:17:02,031 --> 02:17:04,124
I'll always love you.

1675
02:17:16,812 --> 02:17:19,440
Love somebody else.

1676
02:17:41,370 --> 02:17:43,702

1677
02:20:59,935 --> 02:21:01,368
They won't try anything.

1678
02:21:01,470 --> 02:21:03,199
Everything's fine. it's all clear.

1679
02:21:03,972 --> 02:21:06,668
I've already sent Al Neri to the Vatican.

1680
02:21:18,954 --> 02:21:22,890
Mr. Lucchesi's house?

1681
02:21:23,292 --> 02:21:28,127
I bring a message from Michael Corleone.

1682
02:21:28,897 --> 02:21:30,922
Let him in.

1683
02:22:59,488 --> 02:23:00,853
Buona sera.

1684
02:26:22,389 --> 02:26:25,017
Good. You got him.

1685
02:27:16,611 --> 02:27:19,546
Tonight the Corleone family settles its accounts.

1686
02:27:20,315 --> 02:27:22,044
keinszig...

1687
02:27:22,617 --> 02:27:25,916
That little Swiss banker fuck.

1688
02:27:26,187 --> 02:27:31,022
He's been swindling everyone from the beginning. Fuck him.

1689
02:27:31,626 --> 02:27:34,322
Don Lucchesi, my friend.

1690
02:27:34,429 --> 02:27:38,661
Calo will pay him a visit at his home.

1691
02:27:39,768 --> 02:27:41,292
Neri,

1692
02:27:41,636 --> 02:27:43,604
take a train to Rome.

1693
02:27:44,673 --> 02:27:47,506
Light a candle for the Archbishop.

1694
02:28:23,244 --> 02:28:27,203
Tea, Your Holiness? it will help you sleep.

1695
02:28:48,970 --> 02:28:51,939
This is from Vincent Corleone.

1696
02:29:50,298 --> 02:29:55,292
it's serious. Our man inside the Vatican says there's a plot against the Pope.

1697
02:29:55,403 --> 02:29:58,133
He'll have a heart attack?

1698
02:30:04,512 --> 02:30:07,003
This Pope has powerful enemies.

1699
02:30:07,115 --> 02:30:10,243
We may not be in time to save him.

1700
02:30:12,654 --> 02:30:14,679
Let's go back.

1701
02:30:48,923 --> 02:30:50,515
Eminenza...

1702
02:30:56,197 --> 02:31:01,191

1703
02:31:04,405 --> 02:31:09,502
The Holy Father is dead!

1704
02:32:39,067 --> 02:32:40,432
Sleep.

1705
02:32:41,302 --> 02:32:43,600
Sleep, Godfather.

1706
02:33:53,541 --> 02:33:55,566
Speak...tell me.

1707
02:33:55,677 --> 02:34:01,115
You have lost

1708
02:34:01,215 --> 02:34:03,581
the faith of the people.

1709
02:34:05,019 --> 02:34:08,716
He who builds on the people builds on mud.

1710
02:34:09,323 --> 02:34:14,351
And Michael Corleone's message?

1711
02:34:28,376 --> 02:34:33,541
it's very important.

1712
02:34:33,681 --> 02:34:37,879
I must whisper it in your ear.

1713
02:34:40,922 --> 02:34:43,015
He's clean.

1714
02:35:00,708 --> 02:35:03,506
Power wears out those who don't have it.

1715
02:36:32,300 --> 02:36:34,666
-I like this outfit.
-I figured you would.

1716
02:36:34,802 --> 02:36:36,963
Say hello.

1717
02:36:59,460 --> 02:37:00,859
Can I talk to you now?

1718
02:37:00,962 --> 02:37:03,123
No, it's not a good time.

1719
02:37:03,297 --> 02:37:04,491
You're just like my father.

1720
02:37:04,532 --> 02:37:07,365
Stay with the family. Go on.

1721
02:37:08,736 --> 02:37:10,636
-Talk to me.
-The twins are dead.

1722
02:37:10,738 --> 02:37:14,504
in about one minute, there will be carabinieri all over this place.

1723
02:37:15,710 --> 02:37:20,477
Get everybody to the cars, quietly.

1724
02:37:35,229 --> 02:37:38,630
The name Corleone will be associated with a voice.

1725
02:37:48,075 --> 02:37:49,474
Dad...

1726
02:38:09,430 --> 02:38:13,423
Dad... Why are you doing this to me?

1727
02:38:22,410 --> 02:38:25,470
Move back, move back.

1728
02:38:25,613 --> 02:38:27,979
You don't have to do this to me.

1729
02:38:28,082 --> 02:38:34,021
Do what? What do you mean?

1730
02:38:56,610 --> 02:38:58,635
Dad...

1731
02:39:08,456 --> 02:39:14,452

1732
02:39:14,862 --> 02:39:19,026
No! Mary!

1733
02:39:19,133 --> 02:39:23,263
God, no!

